FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - ARGENTINA (BUENOS AIRES):
SUSPECTED
***********
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Thu, 6 Jun 2002 17:49:44 -0700
From: "Pablo Nart" <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: OIE 3 June 2002

(Date of previous reported outbreak: January 2002).
Translation of information received on 6 June 2002 from Dr Bernardo
Gabriel Cane, President, National Agrifood Health and Quality Service
(SENASA), Secretariat for Agriculture, Livestock, Fisheries and Food,
Buenos Aires:
On 30 May 2002, in the province of Buenos Aires, during inspection of
a bovine herd being sent to a sale barn, lesions were discovered in the
buccal cavities of these animals.
On 31 May 2002, 217 bovines from the concerned farm were inspected
and possible Foot and Mouth Disease lesions were found on 55 calves.
Epithelium and blood samples have been collected for laboratory
testing.
Appropriate sanitary measures have been immediately undertaken and
an epidemiological investigation has started while awaiting the
laboratory results.
Animal Health Information Department
Office International des Epizooties (OIE)
<information.dept@oie.int>
... Further details will be published in the next issue of Weekly Disease
Information, available on line as from Friday 7 June 2002 afternoon
(GMT).
